<paragraph blockId="5.[272,1055,1242,1298]" box="[564,750,1274,1298]" pageId="5" pageNumber="2406">
(
<figureCitation box="[572,681,1274,1298]" captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="5.[125,194,961,980]" captionTargetBox="[125,1171,134,925]" captionTargetId="figure-68@5.[125,1173,134,925]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 1–4. Wing patterns. (1) Parastegana (Allstegana) drosophiloides (Toda and Peng). (2) Parastegana (Allstegana) maculipennis (Okada). (3) Parastegana (Allstegana) brevivena Chen and Zhang, sp. nov. (4) Parastegana (Allstegana) punctalata Chen and Watabe, sp. nov. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658284/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="2406">Figures 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[696,740,1274,1298]" captionStart="Figures 5–9" captionStartId="6.[138,207,967,986]" captionTargetBox="[142,1180,138,927]" captionTargetId="figure-147@6.[138,1186,133,931]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figures 5–9. Male terminalia of Parastegana (Allstegana) brevivena Chen and Zhang, sp. nov. (5) Epandrium (epand), cercus (cerc), and surstylus (sur). (6, 7) Hypandrium (hypd), gonopods (gon), parameres (pm), aedeagus (aed), and aedeagal apodeme (aed a), ventral and lateral views, respectively. (8) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (9) Hypoproct. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658286/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="2406">5–9</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[125,245,1355,1379]" box="[125,245,1355,1379]" pageId="5" pageNumber="2406">
<emphasis box="[125,245,1355,1379]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="2406">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[125,1136,1404,1428]" box="[125,1136,1404,1428]" pageId="5" pageNumber="2406">
<emphasis box="[125,194,1404,1428]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="2406">Head.</emphasis>
Frons brown. Face and clypeus yellow-brown. Gena brown-red. Palpus yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[125,1172,1468,1556]" pageId="5" pageNumber="2406">
<emphasis box="[125,214,1468,1492]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="2406">Thorax.</emphasis>
Mesonotum yellow, with three obscure brown, longitudinal stripes on posterior half; median stripe posteriorly triangularly broadened. Pleura brown. Scutellum dark brown, pale on tip.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[125,765,1596,1623]" box="[125,765,1596,1623]" pageId="5" pageNumber="2406">
<emphasis box="[125,193,1596,1620]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="2406">Wing.</emphasis>
R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[226,258,1606,1623]" fontSize="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="2406">2+3</subScript>
with a short branch subapically (
<figureCitation box="[650,751,1596,1620]" captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="5.[125,194,961,980]" captionTargetBox="[125,1171,134,925]" captionTargetId="figure-68@5.[125,1173,134,925]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 1–4. Wing patterns. (1) Parastegana (Allstegana) drosophiloides (Toda and Peng). (2) Parastegana (Allstegana) maculipennis (Okada). (3) Parastegana (Allstegana) brevivena Chen and Zhang, sp. nov. (4) Parastegana (Allstegana) punctalata Chen and Watabe, sp. nov. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658284/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="2406">Figure 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[125,342,1661,1685]" lastBlockId="6.[138,1185,1141,1230]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="2407" pageId="5" pageNumber="2406">
<emphasis box="[125,183,1662,1685]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="2406">Legs.</emphasis>
Yellow-grey. 
<emphasis box="[138,249,1141,1165]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="2407">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Male: first tergite yellow-brown; the others brown; first to fifth sternites yellow. Female: all tergites yellow-brown; first to fifth sternites yellow; sixth and seventh yellowbrown.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658286" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4658286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658286/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="2407" startId="6.[138,207,967,986]" targetBox="[142,1180,138,927]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[138,1185,967,1065]" pageId="6" pageNumber="2407">
Figures 5–9. Male terminalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen and Zhang" authorityName="Chen and Zhang" authorityYear="2007" box="[454,944,967,986]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Parastegana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="2407" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevivena" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Allstegana">
<emphasis box="[454,561,967,986]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="2407">Parastegana</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[578,668,967,986]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="2407">Allstegana</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[685,769,967,986]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="2407">brevivena</emphasis>
Chen and Zhang
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[957,1034,967,986]" pageId="6" pageNumber="2407" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(5) Epandrium (epand), cercus (cerc), and surstylus (sur). (6, 7) Hypandrium (hypd), gonopods (gon), parameres (pm), aedeagus (aed), and aedeagal apodeme (aed a), ventral and lateral views, respectively. (8) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (9) Hypoproct. Scale bars: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="6.[138,1185,1270,1359]" pageId="6" pageNumber="2407">
<emphasis box="[138,324,1270,1294]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="2407">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Cercus rounded ventrally in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[830,930,1270,1294]" captionStart="Figures 5–9" captionStartId="6.[138,207,967,986]" captionTargetBox="[142,1180,138,927]" captionTargetId="figure-147@6.[138,1186,133,931]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figures 5–9. Male terminalia of Parastegana (Allstegana) brevivena Chen and Zhang, sp. nov. (5) Epandrium (epand), cercus (cerc), and surstylus (sur). (6, 7) Hypandrium (hypd), gonopods (gon), parameres (pm), aedeagus (aed), and aedeagal apodeme (aed a), ventral and lateral views, respectively. (8) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (9) Hypoproct. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658286/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="2407">Figure 5</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus rough on surface (
<figureCitation box="[237,377,1303,1327]" captionStart="Figures 5–9" captionStartId="6.[138,207,967,986]" captionTargetBox="[142,1180,138,927]" captionTargetId="figure-147@6.[138,1186,133,931]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figures 5–9. Male terminalia of Parastegana (Allstegana) brevivena Chen and Zhang, sp. nov. (5) Epandrium (epand), cercus (cerc), and surstylus (sur). (6, 7) Hypandrium (hypd), gonopods (gon), parameres (pm), aedeagus (aed), and aedeagal apodeme (aed a), ventral and lateral views, respectively. (8) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (9) Hypoproct. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658286/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="2407">Figures 6–8</figureCitation>
). Paramere proximally broad, submedially deeply concaved in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[207,307,1335,1359]" captionStart="Figures 5–9" captionStartId="6.[138,207,967,986]" captionTargetBox="[142,1180,138,927]" captionTargetId="figure-147@6.[138,1186,133,931]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figures 5–9. Male terminalia of Parastegana (Allstegana) brevivena Chen and Zhang, sp. nov. (5) Epandrium (epand), cercus (cerc), and surstylus (sur). (6, 7) Hypandrium (hypd), gonopods (gon), parameres (pm), aedeagus (aed), and aedeagal apodeme (aed a), ventral and lateral views, respectively. (8) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (9) Hypoproct. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658286/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="2407">Figure 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[138,1128,1400,1424]" box="[138,1128,1400,1424]" pageId="6" pageNumber="2407">
<emphasis box="[138,345,1400,1424]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="2407">Female terminalia.</emphasis>
Hypoproct pubescent, setulose, subcaudally with setae (
<figureCitation box="[1012,1113,1400,1424]" captionStart="Figures 5–9" captionStartId="6.[138,207,967,986]" captionTargetBox="[142,1180,138,927]" captionTargetId="figure-147@6.[138,1186,133,931]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figures 5–9. Male terminalia of Parastegana (Allstegana) brevivena Chen and Zhang, sp. nov. (5) Epandrium (epand), cercus (cerc), and surstylus (sur). (6, 7) Hypandrium (hypd), gonopods (gon), parameres (pm), aedeagus (aed), and aedeagal apodeme (aed a), ventral and lateral views, respectively. (8) Aedeagus, dorsal view. (9) Hypoproct. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658286/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="2407">Figure 9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
